BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:xQXnDmyBEpF-XpPEONq4D
SUMMARY:Woodinville Half
DTSTAMP:20260307T061522Z
DTSTART:20260308T150000Z
DESCRIPTION:Kirk-Wood Half is now the Woodinville Half Hello runners\, We k
	now many of you have been looking forward to the Kirk-Wood Half Marathon\,
	 and we appreciate your understanding as we share an important update rega
	rding the event. Unfortunately\, we have had to change the route for the K
	irk-Wood Half due to ongoing construction on the Kirkland Cross Corridor T
	rail.  The good news: the half marathon will still take place on Sunday\, 
	March 8 — just with an updated route. The event will now start and finish 
	at Wilmot Park\, which was originally planned as the finish line. This eli
	minates the need for participant shuttles and allows us to offer a flat\, 
	fast\, and fun course. We are incredibly grateful for the support and flex
	ibility shown by the City of Woodinville and King County Parks in making t
	his possible. At this time\, our focus is on delivering an exceptional rac
	e experience on March 8. The City of Kirkland has indicated a willingness 
	to permit the event on a future date\, and we are exploring the possibilit
	y of hosting the Kirk-Wood Half Marathon later this year. Important Update
	s: The event will now be called the Woodinville Half Marathon. All partici
	pants will receive a free slice of pizza from The Pizza Coup post-race  . 
	All participants will still receive a full-zip hooded sweatshirt with regi
	stration. We will be updating the design. View the new course map: https:/
	/www.mapmyrun.com/routes/view/6667331427 Thank you for your continued supp
	ort\, we can’t wait to see you at the start line! Sincerely\, Grant Harrin
	gton Owner Snohomish Running Company\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/event
	s/#/details/woodinville-half/18291053/2026-03-08T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Spo
	rts & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/woodinville-half/18291053
	/2026-03-08T00
LOCATION:Kirkland Marina Park\, 25 Lakeshore Plz Dr\, Kirkland\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:uahbBFNdkJn-ws8szyMPd
SUMMARY:WA Concealed Carry Class at Wildlife Committee of
DTSTAMP:20260307T061522Z
DTSTART:20260308T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:This 4-hour comprehensive training course is designed to educat
	e individuals on the laws and regulations surrounding the carrying of conc
	ealed firearms. This class covers essential topics such as the use of forc
	e\, firearms safety\, and the proper handling and storage of firearms\, as
	 well as the specific laws and any requirements for obtaining permits in W
	ashington\, Oregon\, Arizona\, and Utah. Upon completion of the class\, at
	tendees will be eligible to apply for the above-mentioned permits. You wil
	l also receive a WA - HB-1143 Gun Safety Certificate. DATES and TIMES are 
	subject to change\, please view our website for the most up to date and ac
	curate class info. https://www.legalheat.com/classes/in-person/concealed-c
	arry-class-at-wildlife-committee-of-washington-bothell-wa/?utm\\_source=fa
	cebook&utm\\_medium=event\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details
	/wa-concealed-carry-class-at-wildlife-committee-of/18252325/2026-03-08T00\
	n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/wa-concealed-carry-class-
	at-wildlife-committee-of/18252325/2026-03-08T00
LOCATION:Wildlife Committee of Washington - WCWShootingSports - Kenmore Ran
	ge\, 1031 228th St SW\, Bothell\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
